1:1 COMMENT "# generator_listiter.z -- container iterator written as a generator."
1:69 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# Same shape as listiter.z's bag-with-iterator demo, but the"
3:61 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# iterator is implemented as a one-line generator method instead"
4:65 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# of a hand-rolled BagIter class. Observable output matches"
5:60 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# listiter.z byte-for-byte (see tests/test_generator_validation.py)."
6:69 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "#"
7:2 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# Encapsulation: `public: unit { :count :iterate }` hides the"
8:62 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# private fields a/b/c; the generator method takes the receiver as"
9:67 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# `b: this.private.lock` so the synth class can read those private"
10:67 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "# fields. The factory's external signature is `b: this.lock`"
11:61 EOL "\n"
12:1 COMMENT "# (public) -- the desugarer (P7) projects `.private` when"
12:58 EOL "\n"
13:1 COMMENT "# forwarding to the synth-class instance, the same trick the"
13:61 EOL "\n"
14:1 COMMENT "# hand-written `examples/listiter.z` uses"
14:42 EOL "\n"
15:1 COMMENT "# (`return BagIter target: b.private`)."
15:40 EOL "\n"
16:1 COMMENT "#"
16:2 EOL "\n"
17:1 COMMENT "# What the desugarer builds underneath:"
17:40 EOL "\n"
18:1 COMMENT "#   - A class `Bag_iterate_iter` with `state: i64` and a"
18:57 EOL "\n"
19:1 COMMENT "#     `b: Bag.private.lock` field."
19:35 EOL "\n"
20:1 COMMENT "#   - A factory function `Bag.iterate` with `b: this.lock`"
20:59 EOL "\n"
21:1 COMMENT "#     externally; body projects `.private` on the forward."
21:59 EOL "\n"
22:1 COMMENT "#   - The class's `.call` method implements the iterator protocol"
22:66 EOL "\n"
23:1 COMMENT "#     structurally via a switch/goto state machine."
23:52 EOL "\n"
24:1 EOL "\n"
